&lt;h2 id="three-theme-modes"&gt;
 Three Theme Modes
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Click the toggle in the header to cycle through:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Retro&lt;/strong&gt; (gamepad) — NES deep-blue background, pixel font headings, 8-bit dialog borders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Light&lt;/strong&gt; (sun) — clean, modern light palette&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dark&lt;/strong&gt; (moon) — comfortable for night reading&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2 id="writing"&gt;
 Writing
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Regular Markdown works as expected. &lt;strong&gt;Bold text&lt;/strong&gt; stands out in gold under retro mode, and &lt;em&gt;italic text&lt;/em&gt; stays readable. You can link to &lt;a href="https://sothawang.github.io/"&gt;any page&lt;/a&gt; and the style adapts per theme.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Code Samples</title><link>https://sothawang.github.io/posts/code-samples/</link><pubDate>Sun, 19 Oct 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://sothawang.github.io/posts/code-samples/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="javascript"&gt;
